State files an Amended Information charging 3 cts. misdemeanor theft, contrary to Section 943.20(1)(d) of the Wisconsin Statutes.  Motion granted.  Guilty pleas to the amended charges.  Convicted.  Sentences are withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years.  Conditions of probation are:
1) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination;
3) Pay restitution of $1,675.97 to Jacob Charnon, 4080 Lancer Circle, Manitowoc, WI  54220.  $500.00 is to be paid within the first ten days and then $70.00 per month starting in January, 2015 and each month thereafter.  
4) Thirty (30 ) days jail, twenty-five (25) days jail stayed, to be imposed upon the agent's discretion.  Five (5) days, under the Huber Law, to commence on 01-06-15 at 8:00 a.m.  
5) Pay costs of action; 
6) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
7) Have no contact with the victim.
Court finds that defendant will benefit and society will not be harmed by expungment of record pursuant to Section 973.015 of the Wisconsin Statutes upon successful completion of sentence.  
